<li id="cite_note-obit-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-obit_27-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/books/97/03/30/reviews/chaplin-obit.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/books/97/03/30/reviews/chaplin-obit.html" rel="nofollow">"Charlie Chaplin Dead at 88; Made the Film an Art Form."</a>. <a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" title="New York Times" class="mw-redirect">New York Times</a>. 26 December 1977, Monday<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/books/97/03/30/reviews/chaplin-obit.html" class="external free" title="http://www.nytimes.com/books/97/03/30/reviews/chaplin-obit.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/books/97/03/30/reviews/chaplin-obit.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-08-21</span>.  "Charlie Chaplin, the poignant little tramp with the cane and comic walk who almost single-handedly elevated the novelty entertainment medium of motion pictures into art, died peacefully yesterday at his home in Switzerland. He was 88 years old."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Charlie+Chaplin+Dead+at+88%3B+Made+the+Film+an+Art+Form.&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=26+December+1977%2C+Monday&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BNew+York+Times%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fbooks%2F97%2F03%2F30%2Freviews%2Fchaplin-obit.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Charlie_Chaplin"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
