<li><i><a href="/wiki/Chaplin:_His_Life_and_Art" title="Chaplin: His Life and Art">Chaplin: His Life and Art</a></i>, David Robinson. McGraw-Hill, second edition 2001.</li>
<li><i>Chaplin: Genius of the Cinema</i>, Jeffrey Vance. Abrams, New York, 2003.</li>
<li><i>Charlie Chaplin: A Photo Diary</i>, Michel Comte &amp; Sam Stourdze. Steidl, first edition, hardcover, 359pp, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/3882437928" class="internal">ISBN 388-243-7928</a>, 2002.</li>
<li><a href="http://journal.media-culture.org.au/0411/05-goldman.php" class="external autonumber" title="http://journal.media-culture.org.au/0411/05-goldman.php" rel="nofollow">[1]</a><i>Double Exposure: Charlie Chaplin as Author and Celebrity</i>, Jonathan Goldman. <u>M/C Journal</u> 7.5.</li>
</ul>
